§ About the Role §
This is a customer success management (CSM) role to support sales finding out new opportunities, which would be whitespot hunting, strategic initiatives, new products evaluation, and new MCI (market & consumer intelligence) approaching. This role is to work closely with country lead and sales team to develop the new business/initiatives.
The key focuses would be MI (market intelligence) for new products evaluation, such as Engine oil, car/scooter battery, sanitary, and MCI for car manufacturers, and whitespot hunting for current existing MI report.

§ Key Responsibilities §
1. In depth study and logical recommendation to Country Lead what new products should be start up;
2. Develop and manage the local country road map together;
3. To learn and master key industries knowledge and understand the dynamics of the business in the industry, mapping out the approach to each industry. Knowing key target contacts and associations as well as local or regional fairs that is crucial for the business;
4. Defend GfK from industry competitor surfacing;
5. Identify approaches to counter competition if any;
6. Attract industry attention and develop appeal to them;
7. Built a reputation for GfK in the industry we intend to develop as a crucial source of information for the industry business as well as a benchmark.

